&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Figma is growing our team of passionate creatives and builders on a mission to make design accessible to all. Figma’s platform helps teams bring ideas to life—whether you&#39;re brainstorming, creating a prototype, translating designs into code, or iterating with AI. From idea to product, Figma empowers teams to streamline workflows, move faster, and work together in real time from anywhere in the world. If you&#39;re excited to shape the future of design and collaboration, join us!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Figma Sites is one of our newest products, currently in public beta. It helps creators turn their designs into beautiful, performant websites in just a few clicks — no plugins, code exports, or handoffs required. We’re building the future of “design to product,” and Sites is central to that mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Product Manager to help own the next chapter of Figma Sites as we move from public beta to general availability. This role is ideal for a builder who thrives at the intersection of design, development, and innovation. You’ll help define the vision, influence company-wide strategy, and deliver experiences that make it effortless to go from idea to live site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time role that can be held from one of our US hubs or remotely in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do at Figma:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evolve the strategy for Figma Sites, driving adoption and impact as we scale from beta to general availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with engineering, design, and research to deliver seamless publishing, responsive design, and creative tooling experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional alignment across multiple teams — including Figma Design and Figma Make — to enable a flawless “design to production” workflow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather user insights from our growing community and translate them into clear priorities and product decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape how AI and prompting enhance creativity, customization, and accessibility in Sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Figma Sites across the company, helping drive vision, prioritization, and execution for one of Figma’s most strategic bets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’d love to hear from you if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
